I have such wonderful memories dining here throughout the years and I'm so happy places like The Bagel 🥯 still exist.  My mother used to treat me here as a teenager to good food  like sandwiches,  traditional Jewish appetizers, kreplach soup and dessert at the former location in Skokie.  I felt nostalgia and came here today on purpose to fulfill some of my Jewish cuisine cravings.  Both the owner Danny Wolf and my lovely server Erika greeted me with genuine enthusiasm when I arrived for dinner here.  All I knew upon entering was that I had to order a kishke so Erika gave me plenty of time to decide while she brought me out their traditional platter of sliced dill pickles, toasted homemade bagel thins and their yummy challah bread slices 🍞 with 🧈 butter. I'm a foodie so I appreciate good food prepared with love, a friendly staff and the coziness factor of where I'm dining. I also love the booths here and retro 1950s diner energies. The Bagel 🥯 never disappoints and I chose a potato 🥔 pancake with apple 🍎 sauce and sourcream, a meat filled knish and the kishke I'd been craving for days.  The vibes here were positive and I thoroughly enjoyed conversing with everyone here so another waiter Chris made sure to write ✍ everyone's names here so I could write the review tonight as a ❤ genuine heartfelt than you 🙏 for showing me such a good time today. I wish The Bagel team continued success for years to come and next time I'll definitely pop in for lunch and try one of their famous deli style sandwiches 😋

I was SO excited to try this place when I moved to this part of town. But now I'm convinced I must have gotten the bagel buzz confused and people were suggesting CBA and not this place. The service was slow (which is forgivable), but everything after that was bad. I ordered an egg sandwich on a croissant because they didn't have many appealing bagel options, which was a huge let down. The croissant was not fresh at all. It was crumbly instead of flaky which made a huge mess in addition to being gross. I was starving but could only eat half of it. The process to get our check and pay took way longer than it should have on a slow Sunday afternoon (well after the morning/noon rush). And if you park in their lot, be prepared to get a boot on your car and forced to pay $130. Once the boot is on, there's nothing management can do because they don't maintain nor have authority over their own parking lot. It's kind of the worst and I'm not sure how they're in business. Makes you wonder... With all this competition. Hmmm... Super sketchy. I'll never go back.
